Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.62,0:00:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's Princess Luna and {\i0}\N{\i1}Princess Celestia.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.81,0:00:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,They're missing!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.99,0:00:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The Everfree Forest is\N{\i1}... invading.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.90,0:00:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I think I'm starting to{\i0}\N{\i1}get a pretty good idea{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.57,0:00:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}of who we're up against.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.26,0:00:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm reformed; don't\Nyou remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.47,0:00:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't you ask\Nyour zebra friend?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.42,0:00:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You can turn the potion\Nfrom purple to white.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.14,0:00:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You may see why the sky is day
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.10,0:00:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and night.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.77,0:00:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Princess Luna!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.72,0:00:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,There can only be one\Nprincess in Equestria!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.07,0:00:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And that princess will be me!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.76,0:00:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Subtitles by YayPonies\Nhttp://yayponies.eu
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.14,0:01:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Luna! Think of how long you\Nwere banished to the moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.26,0:01:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll give us no choice but\Nto send you back there
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.59,0:01:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,if you don't stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.05,0:01:51.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Luna, I will not fight you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.54,0:01:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You must lower the moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.62,0:01:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It is your duty.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.38,0:02:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,"Luna", I am Nightmare Moon!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.61,0:02:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I have but one royal duty\Nnow: to destroy you!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.44,0:02:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And where do you\Nthink you're going?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.33,0:02:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Celestia!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.86,0:02:39.49,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.55,0:02:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would Luna do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.54,0:02:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Why now?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.16,0:02:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You're all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.97,0:02:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You're all right!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.32,0:02:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Princess Celestia?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.16,0:03:01.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, dear, sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.88,0:03:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I am sorry, but you have given\Nme no choice but to use these.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.76,0:03:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Are those...the\NElements of Harmony?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.18,0:03:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's how\Nthey looked in...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.11,0:03:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.84,0:03:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the night\Nyou banished her.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.85,0:04:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Noooooo!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.55,0:04:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you all looking\Nat me like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.45,0:04:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just you were\Nmumblin' to yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.91,0:04:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, and don't forget the\Nuncontrollable sobbing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.43,0:04:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We were really\Nworried about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.60,0:04:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I, for one, found it {\i0}\N{\i1}delightful.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.43,0:04:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Sort of a one-pony theater\Npiece, if you will.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.91,0:04:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You should really consider\Ntaking it on the road.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.81,0:04:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you find out whose\Nrump we need to kick?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.73,0:04:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And where we can find 'em?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.50,0:04:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw something from\Na long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.77,0:04:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,But it didn't explain\Nwhat's happening now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.12,0:04:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps farther back still\Nare the answers you seek.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.15,0:05:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Another sip of the potion{\i0}\N{\i1}will give you a peek.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.38,0:05:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sure about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.01,0:05:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I do hope she breaks\Ninto a song this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.51,0:05:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Ho ho! Ho ho ! This\Nis so much fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.96,0:05:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,How about a game of\Npin-the-tail-on-the-pony?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.56,0:05:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Play time is over\Nfor you, Discord.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.28,0:05:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I doubt that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.05,0:05:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Hungry?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.51,0:05:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Suit yourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.04,0:05:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Oooh. What have\Nyou got there?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.89,0:06:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The Elements of Harmony.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.23,0:06:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,With them we shall defeat you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.18,0:06:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,This must be when they turn\NDiscord into stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.04,0:06:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You should see\Nyourselves right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.98,0:06:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The expressions on your face.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.94,0:06:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}So intense. So sure{\i0}\N{\i1}of yourselves.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.04,0:06:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Ah ha ha!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.39,0:06:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Hilarious!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.11,0:06:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The Tree of Harmony.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.61,0:06:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The Tree of Harmony?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.43,0:06:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,My Cutie Mark.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.92,0:06:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.85,0:06:57.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We have managed to\Ndiscover the only means
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.14,0:06:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,by which we can\Ndefeat Discord
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.10,0:07:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and free the citizens\Nof Equestria.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.09,0:07:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Even without these elements,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.78,0:07:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}the Tree of Harmony will{\i0}\N{\i1}possess a powerful magic.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.73,0:07:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}As long as that{\i0}\N{\i1}magic remains,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.57,0:07:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,it will continue to control and\Ncontain all that grows here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.55,0:07:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what did\Nyou find out?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.36,0:07:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I still don't know what's\Nhappened to Princess Luna
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.36,0:07:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and Princess Celestia,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.41,0:07:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,but I think I know why\Nthe Everfree Forest
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.11,0:07:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is acting this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.09,0:07:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Something's happened\Nto the Tree of Harmony.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.90,0:07:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The Tree of what now?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.74,0:07:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It's where Princess Celestia\Nand Princess Luna
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.76,0:07:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,found the Elements.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.82,0:07:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's in danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.58,0:07:47.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, all right then,\Nlet's go save a...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.88,0:07:49.01,Default,,0,0,0,,tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.05,0:07:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, where is it exactly?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.61,0:07:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's in ...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.50,0:07:54.37,Default,,0,0,0,,...there !
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.77,0:07:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Hoo hoo!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.64,0:08:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to need\Nmore popcorn.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.36,0:08:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Seems like only yesterday we\Nwere heading into these woods
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.96,0:08:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,to find the Elements\Nof Harmony.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.91,0:08:18.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Seems like only yesterday\NI was foolish enough
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.04,0:08:20.18,Default,,0,0,0,,to think I should go\Nafter them on my own.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.90,0:08:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what we're\Ngoing to face in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.18,0:08:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But whatever it is, I know\Nwe need to face it together.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.49,0:08:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We can use those to cross.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.70,0:09:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That was close.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.52,0:09:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,A little too close\Nif you ask me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.60,0:09:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You sure you're\Nall right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.19,0:09:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.18,0:09:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I just can't seem to get\Nthese new wings to do
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.58,0:09:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,what I want them to do\Nwhen I want them to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.20,0:09:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Aw, you'll figure\Nit out eventually.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.36,0:09:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,"Eventually" isn't soon enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.67,0:09:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You have been havin' an awful\Nlot of trouble with those things
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.82,0:09:30.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and well, who knows what\Nelse is gonna come after us.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.63,0:09:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, maybe it wouldn't\Nbe such a bad idea
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.02,0:09:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,for Twilight to go\Nback to Ponyville
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.59,0:09:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and let us look for the Tree\Nof Harmony without her.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.97,0:09:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.53,0:09:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,For starters, you just about\Ngot eaten by a Cragidile.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.59,0:09:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We all did.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.73,0:09:44.41,Default,,0,0,0,,He wasn't after\Njust me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.63,0:09:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure. But... well, the rest of\Nus aren't princesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.85,0:09:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that got\Nto do with anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.01,0:09:53.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Princess Celestia and\NPrincess Luna are gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.86,0:09:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,If something happened to you,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.53,0:09:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I just don't think Equestria can\Nrisk losin' another Princess.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.78,0:10:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Applejack does\Nmake a valid point.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.15,0:10:03.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if we manage to\Nsave the Tree of Harmony,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.42,0:10:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,it won't necessarily\Nmean Princess Celestia
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.23,0:10:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and Princess Luna\Nwill return.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.94,0:10:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Equestria will need somepony\Nto lead in their absence.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.26,0:10:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But the Tree of Harmony.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.75,0:10:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm the only one who has seen it\Nand knows what it looks like.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.64,0:10:16.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Huge tree. Cutie\NMarks on the trunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.94,0:10:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably being attacked by\Nsomething hideously awful.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.63,0:10:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I'm pretty sure we'll\Nknow it when we see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.75,0:10:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,All of you feel this way?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.76,0:10:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Feel like I shouldn't be here?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.57,0:10:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It is probably\Nfor the best.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.89,0:10:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Help! Help!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.84,0:10:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Discord!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.84,0:10:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You're welcome!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.70,0:10:53.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.74,0:10:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,No luck finding your tree?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.40,0:11:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We ran into some trouble and my\Nfriends decided it would be best
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.05,0:11:02.49,Default,,0,0,0,,if I returned to Ponyville\Nwhile they continue the search.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.96,0:11:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Equestria will need me if\NPrincess Celestia
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.88,0:11:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and Princess Luna\Ndon't return.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.01,0:11:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just surprised that\Nyou agreed to their plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.67,0:11:11.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I never thought you'd\Nbe the kind of pony
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.54,0:11:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,who would think she was\Nbetter than everypony else.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.95,0:11:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think I'm\Nbetter than anypony.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.70,0:11:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! Well, how silly of me to\Nassume you would think that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.36,0:11:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,All you did was choose to keep\Nyour precious Princess-self
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.11,0:11:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,out of harm's way while your\Nfriends thrust themselves
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.27,0:11:29.33,Default,,0,0,0,,right into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.74,0:11:33.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'm sure you'll all be{\i0}\N{\i1}the best of pals again{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.10,0:11:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}when they return from{\i0}\N{\i1}their terrifying,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.25,0:11:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}yet deeply bonding{\i0}\N{\i1}experience{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.88,0:11:40.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}that they're having{\i0}\N{\i1}without you.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.92,0:11:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I never should have\Nagreed to come back here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.86,0:11:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, Twilight,\NDiscord may be reformed
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.72,0:11:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,but he's not that reformed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.28,0:11:53.31,Default,,0,0,0,,He's just trying to\Nget under your skin.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.67,0:11:55.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's working!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.75,0:12:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Anypony else starting to\Nthink this is a lost cause?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.15,0:12:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We're almost at Celestia\Nand Luna's old castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.90,0:12:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe whatever\NTwilight saw
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.37,0:12:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,when she took that crazy\Npotion wasn't real.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.28,0:12:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe there is no\NTree of Harmony. Maybe--
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.61,0:12:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe it's\Nright down there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.43,0:12:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It can't be.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.55,0:12:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,How are we supposed\Nto get to it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.90,0:12:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Take the stairs, silly!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.43,0:12:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Are we there yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.08,0:12:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know where\Nwe are. We're lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.80,0:12:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I never should've\Nleft my friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.24,0:12:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't just give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.99,0:12:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe if I get up there,\NI'll be able to spot 'em.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.71,0:12:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what do you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.89,0:12:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Twilight!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.48,0:13:04.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Fluttershy: I think it's dying!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.94,0:13:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's save it already.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.84,0:13:10.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Oof!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.39,0:13:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice try.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.28,0:13:15.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.42,0:13:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Oof!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.49,0:13:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Valiant effort on\Nboth your parts,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.12,0:13:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,but the tree\Nremains in jeopardy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.28,0:13:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And I suppose you've\Ngot a better idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.16,0:13:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.85,0:13:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I know who would\Nknow what to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.14,0:13:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But we sent her home.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.83,0:13:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It was your idea, Applejack!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.55,0:13:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We all agreed it was the\Nbest thing, Rainbow Dash!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.54,0:13:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We were tryin'\Nto protect her.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.86,0:13:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Twilight!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.53,0:13:55.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Trouble!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.35,0:13:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Help!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.16,0:14:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen here, you\Nrabid rhododendrons.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.78,0:14:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You mess with one of us.\NYou mess with all of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.61,0:14:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Up here!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.66,0:14:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Yoo-hoo! Come\Nand get me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.23,0:14:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't forget about me!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.32,0:14:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Ta-da! {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.09,0:14:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I sure am glad you\Ncame lookin' for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.43,0:14:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Not as glad as I am\Nthat you found me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.90,0:14:51.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The truth of it is, Twilight,\Nwe're simply lost without you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.88,0:14:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Equestria may\Nneed its Princess...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.64,0:14:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But we need our friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.16,0:15:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Even without these {\i0}\N{\i1}Elements,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.78,0:15:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}the Tree of Harmony will{\i0}\N{\i1}possess a powerful magic.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.92,0:15:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}As long as that magic remains,{\i0}\N{\i1}it will continue to control{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.39,0:15:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and contain all that grows here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.99,0:15:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I know how we can save the Tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.62,0:15:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to give it the\NElements of Harmony.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.27,0:15:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa. Whoa. Whoa.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.50,0:15:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,How are we supposed\Nto protect Equestria?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.77,0:15:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,How are we meant\Nto rein Discord in
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.60,0:15:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,if we can't use the Elements\Nto turn him back to stone?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.47,0:15:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Twilight, the\NElements of Harmony...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.86,0:15:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,They're what keep us\Nconnected no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.60,0:15:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You're right about\None thing, Applejack.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.73,0:15:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The Elements of Harmony\Ndid bring us together.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.28,0:16:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But it isn't the Elements\Nthat will keep us connected.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.90,0:16:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's our friendship.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.92,0:16:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And it's more important and{\i0}\N{\i1}more powerful than any magic.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.31,0:16:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,My new role in Equestria
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.79,0:16:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,may mean I have to take\Non new responsibilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.41,0:16:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And our friendships\Nmay be tested.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.47,0:16:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But it will never,{\i0}\N{\i1}ever be broken.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.11,0:16:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no time to lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.44,0:16:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Everypony ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.36,0:16:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Ready!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.01,0:17:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, poo!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.17,0:17:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We know how difficult it\Nmust have been for you
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.60,0:17:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,to give up the Elements.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.23,0:17:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It took great courage\Nto relinquish them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.89,0:18:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,What's inside it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.41,0:18:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,How am I supposed to open it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.09,0:18:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Six locks.{\i0}\N{\i1}Six keys.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.24,0:18:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I do not know\Nwhere they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.56,0:18:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But I do know that\Nit is a mystery
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.84,0:18:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,you will not be\Nsolving alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.78,0:18:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Bravo, ladies! Bravo!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.85,0:18:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,How ever did you save\Nthe day this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.27,0:18:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Blast a beastie with your\Nmagic necklaces, I presume?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.04,0:18:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are those little\Ntrinkets of yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.10,0:18:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, the ones you\Nuse to send me back
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.94,0:18:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,to my extremely\Nuncomfortable stone prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.14,0:18:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.26,0:18:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Gone? Ha ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.75,0:18:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Gone?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.15,0:18:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But our friendship remains.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.06,0:19:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you want to\Nremain friends,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.00,0:19:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll stop thinking whatever\Nit is you're thinking
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.17,0:19:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and help us clean up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.47,0:19:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.07,0:19:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,But I don't do windows.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.70,0:19:12.27,Default,,0,0,0,,One thing I don't get.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.36,0:19:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Why'd all this happen now?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.55,0:19:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I have no idea.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.74,0:19:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Those seeds I planted\Nshould've sprouted up ages ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.97,0:19:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.57,0:19:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. Why should I\Ntry to explain it,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.45,0:19:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,when you can see\Nfor yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.35,0:19:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Play time is over\Nfor you, Discord.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.01,0:19:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I doubt that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.72,0:19:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Hungry?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.40,0:19:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, obviously things didn't go\N{\i1}according to my original plan.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.75,0:19:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}My plunderseeds should{\i0}\N{\i1}have stolen the magic{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.41,0:19:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}from the Tree of Harmony{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.40,0:19:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and captured Princess{\i0}\N{\i1}Celestia and Princes Luna{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.64,0:19:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}thousands of moons ago.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.41,0:19:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Alas, it seems the Tree{\i0}\N{\i1}had enough magic{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.26,0:20:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}to keep the seeds from{\i0}\N{\i1}growing up big and strong.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.22,0:20:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Until now, that is.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.48,0:20:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You realize this is information\Nwe could have used hours ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.26,0:20:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And rob you of a valuable\Nlesson about being Princess?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.31,0:20:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,What kind of friend\Ndo you think I am?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.55,0:20:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Citizens of Equestria, it is\Nno longer with a heavy heart,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.43,0:20:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,but with great joy, that\NI raise the summer sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.37,0:20:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,For this celebration\Nnow represents,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.63,0:20:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,not the defeat of\NNightmare Moon,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.28,0:20:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,but the return of my\Nsister, Princess Luna.
